cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper proposes a deep learning architecture for joint classification and localization of abnormalities in mammograms. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, since the proposed method is evaluated on a large multi-center mammography dataset, it may also belong to the medical imaging (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also mentions a novel approach with data-driven decisions, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the cost effectiveness of lesion annotation effort, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
